4) What is the difference between returning a primitive type and returning an object in Java?
-->
| Primitive Return       | Object Return             |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Returns value directly | Returns reference         |
| Example: `int`         | Example: `Student` object |
| No behavior            | Has methods + properties  |

int getNumber() {
    return 10; // primitive
}

Student getStudent() {
    return new Student(); // object
}



5) What are covariant return types in Java, and how are they applied in factory method implementations?
-->Covariant return type allows a subclass to return a more specific type when overriding a method.
    Factory method is a method that creates and returns objects instead of directly using new.

👉 Covariant return type = returning subclass instead of parent

✅ Example
class Animal {}

class Dog extends Animal {}

class Factory {
    Animal create() {
        return new Dog();
    }
}

👉 Parent type return → subclass object returned ✔️


6) How do return types enable polymorphism in Java, particularly in the context of factory methods?
-->👉 Return types allow one method to return different objects

    ✅ Example
    Animal a1 = AnimalFactory.getAnimal("dog");
    Animal a2 = AnimalFactory.getAnimal("cat");
    
    a1.sound(); // Bark
    a2.sound(); // Meow
    
    👉 Same return type (Animal)
    👉 Different behavior (Dog / Cat)
